OL,3,CBirmingham bin workers vote to extend
OL,4,Cstrikes into September
OL,6,FUnite says it "remains fully open to
OL,7,Freturn to negotiations to resolve the
OL,8,Fdispute" but has accused Birmingham
OL,9,FCity Council of "refusing to meet",
OL,10,Fadding the assertion that the local
OL,11,Fauthority "continues to waste millions
OL,12,Ftrying unsuccessfully to break the
OL,13,Fstrike."
OL,15,FWe have approached Birmingham City
OL,16,FCouncil for a response.
OL,18,FPreviously, the council has said that
OL,19,Fit has: "engaged in negotiations with
OL,20,FUnite, but they have rejected our fair
OL,21,Fand reasonable offers.
